We introduce Frequency Automata (FA), a new formal model that combines time and frequency domain representations. A sound translation from Hybrid Automata (HA) to FA is provided, along with a dedicated numerical simulator. Our method offers faster and more accurate simulation, especially in detecting level crossings. Experimental results show that FA outperforms Simulink/Stateflow ${ }^{\circledR}$ by up to $1129 \times$ in execution time and can handle equality guards that Simulink fails to detect. Moon Soo Kim, Avinash Malik, and Partha Roop. 2025. Frequency Automata: A novel formal model of hybrid systems in combined time and frequency domains. In International Conference on Embedded Software (EMSOFT’25), September 28-October 3, 2025, Taipei, Taiwan. ACM, New York, NY, USA, 2 pages. https://doi.org/10.1145/3742874.3756008 • Theory of computation→Automata extensions.